AO221_80 MP IN THE HIGH COURT OF JUDICATURE AT BOMBAY CIVIL APPELLATE JURISDICTION APPEAL FROM ORDER NO.221 OF 1980 M/s. Sherali Khan Mohammed Manekia ... Appellants Versus The State of Maharashtra and others ... Respondents Ms Punita Soni, Advocate i/b. Mr. S.U.Kamdar h/f. M/s. A.N.Banatwala & Co., for the Appellant. Mr. Mahendra Agavekar, Advocate i/b. Mr.M.V.Limaye, for Respondent No.10. Mr. Jaydeep Shringare, Advocate i/b. M/s. Chitnis Vaithy & Co., for the Respondent. CORAM : J. H. BHATIA, J.

DATE : 06TH FEBRUARY 2012 P. C. : This matter was disposed of in the year 1983 and the court receiver was appointed pending the aforesaid Appeal from Order. The suit between the parties has come to an end and the execution proceeding is pending. This matter is shown on Board only for directions in respect of the court receiver s report. . The learned Counsel for the appellant seeks adjournment on the ground that the Senior Counsel, who is to appear, is not available today. On the next date, the appellant shall clarify why the court receiver's report should not be remitted to the executing court for appropriate action. . Stand over to 29.02.2012. (J. H. BHATIA, J)
